hwMplsTpEgressGlobalId.description: The GlobalId is defined to uniquely identify an Ingress LSR operator.This Value idefines a globally unique Attachment Interface Identifier (AII). That AII is composed of three parts: a Global_ID that uniquely identifies an operator, a prefix, and, finally, an attachment circuit identifier.

hwMplsTpIngressGlobalId.description: The GlobalId is defined to uniquely identify an Ingress LSR operator.This Value idefines a globally unique Attachment Interface Identifier (AII). hwMplsTpIngressGlobalId.name: hwMplsTpIngressGlobalId

hwMplsTpLspEntry.description: An entry in this table represents information on a single TP LSP which is represented by a session's index triple (hwMplsTpTunnelIngressInstance, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressInstance, hwMplsTpLspType).

hwMplsTpLspType.name: hwMplsTpLspType

hwMplsTpMib.description: This MIB is used for defining the HUAWEI private extended Transport Profile of Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS-TP) MIB object. All MIB objects are used to describe private managed objects and trap definitions for MPLS-TP.
hwMplsTpMib.name: hwMplsTpMib

hwMplsTpTunnelAdminStatus.description: Indicates the management status of this tunnel.Reference to MPLS-TE-STD-MIB. Options: 1. up(1) -indicates the management status of this tunnel is up. 2. down(2) -indicates the management status of this tunnel is down. 3. testing(3) -indicates the tunnel is used in some test mode.
hwMplsTpTunnelAdminStatus.name: hwMplsTpTunnelAdminStatus

hwMplsTpTunnelDown.description: This notification is generated when a mplsTpTunnelOperStatus object for one of the configured tunnels is about to enter the down state from some other state (but not from the notPresent state). This other state is indicated by the included value of mplsTpTunnelOperStatus.
hwMplsTpTunnelDown.name: hwMplsTpTunnelDown

hwMplsTpTunnelDownClear.description: This notification is generated when a mplsTpTunnelOperStatus object for one of the configured tunnels is about to leave the down state and transition into some other state (but not into the notPresent state). This other state is indicated by the included value of mplsTpTunnelOperStatus.
hwMplsTpTunnelDownClear.name: hwMplsTpTunnelDownClear

hwMplsTpTunnelEgressIndex.description: Identity of the egress LSR associated with this tunnel instance.

hwMplsTpTunnelEgressInstance.description: Uniquely identifies a particular instance of a tunnel between a pair of egress and ingress LSRs.
hwMplsTpTunnelEgressInstance.name: hwMplsTpTunnelEgressInstance

hwMplsTpTunnelEgressLSRId.description: Identity of the egress LSR associated with this tunnel instance.
hwMplsTpTunnelEgressLSRId.name: hwMplsTpTunnelEgressLSRId

hwMplsTpTunnelEntry.description: A tp-tunnel needs to be uniquely identified across an MPLS-TP network. Indexes hwMplsTpTunnelIngressIndex, hwMplsTpTunnelIngressLSRId, hwMplsTpIngressGlobalId, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressIndex, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressLSRId and hwMplsTpEgressGlobalId uniquely identifies a tunnel across an MPLS-TP network. The indexes of this entry are hwMplsTpTunnelIngressIndex, hwMplsTpTunnelIngressLSRId, hwMplsTpIngressGlobalId, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressIndex, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressLSRId and hwMplsTpEgressGlobalId.
hwMplsTpTunnelEntry.name: hwMplsTpTunnelEntry
hwMplsTpTunnelEntry.reference: 1. RFC 2863 - The Interfaces Group MIB, McCloghrie, K., and F. Kastenholtz, June 2000

hwMplsTpTunnelIfName.description: Indicates the tp-tunnel interface name. The object is only valid at the ingress.
hwMplsTpTunnelIfName.name: hwMplsTpTunnelIfName

hwMplsTpTunnelIngressIndex.description: Identity of the ingress LSR associated with this tunnel instance. This value SHOULD be equal to the Tunnel Sender Address in the Sender Template object and MAY be equal to the Extended Tunnel Id field in the SESSION object.
hwMplsTpTunnelIngressIndex.name: hwMplsTpTunnelIngressIndex

hwMplsTpTunnelIngressInstance.description: Uniquely identifies a particular instance of a tunnel between a pair of ingress and egress LSRs.
hwMplsTpTunnelIngressInstance.name: hwMplsTpTunnelIngressInstance

hwMplsTpTunnelIngressLSRId.description: Identity of the ingress LSR associated with this tp-tunnel instance.
hwMplsTpTunnelIngressLSRId.name: hwMplsTpTunnelIngressLSRId

hwMplsTpTunnelOperStatus.description: Indicates the actual operational status of this tunnel, which is but not limited to the status of this tunnel of a certain period.Reference to MPLS-TE-STD-MIB. Options: 1. up(1) -indicates that the operational status of this tunnel is up. 2. down(2) -indicates that the operational status of this tunnel is down. 3. testing(3) -indicates that the tunnel is used in some test mode. 4. unknown(4) -indicates the invalid value. 5. dormant(5) -indicates that the status can not be determined. 6. notPresent(6) -indicates that some component is missing 7. lowerLayerDown(7) -indicates the Down state due to the state of lower layer interfaces.
hwMplsTpTunnelOperStatus.name: hwMplsTpTunnelOperStatus

hwMplsTpTunnelResume.description: This object is used to indicate that data switching from protection Lsp to Working Lsp.
hwMplsTpTunnelResume.name: hwMplsTpTunnelResume

hwMplsTpTunnelSwitch.description: This object is used to indicate that data switching from protection Lsp to Working Lsp.
hwMplsTpTunnelSwitch.name: hwMplsTpTunnelSwitch

hwMplsTpTunnelTable.description: A tp-tunnel needs to be uniquely identified across an MPLS-TP network. The indexes of this table are hwMplsTpTunnelIngressIndex, hwMplsTpTunnelIngressLSRId, hwMplsTpIngressGlobalId, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressIndex, hwMplsTpTunnelEgressLSRId and hwMplsTpEgressGlobalId.
hwMplsTpTunnelTable.name: hwMplsTpTunnelTable
